    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filmless x-ray examination technique which produces images that can be stored as a computer file. Sensed analog signals representing intensity of x-ray photons at all points are converted to digital signals via laser scanning of the image receptor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
